<br>
Call of Heroes summons one character to the location of the magician casting the spell, which can be any point in a given zone.  Any point.  This is something Verant has no control over.<br>
<br>
Succor is controlled locomotion, Call of Heroes is not.  Verant likes control.  Succor they can control, Call of Heroes they cannot.  Thus, Call of Heroes can be exploited, by their definition of exploit, where Succor pretty much does whatever they want it to.<br>
<br>
<br>
You will notice, however, that there are even a few zones (i.e. Veeshan's Peak) where even these spells are not permitted.  So, like everything, if Verant feels it will lessen the content of a zone, they can--and will--turn it off. <p>Shallandra McKnight, Uba Monkey<br>
